The paper deals with information-theoretic security in multiple-access channels, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper focuses on capacity-equivocation regions and information-theoretic bounds. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with secure communication in the presence of eavesdroppers. The third likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper discusses the transmission of multiple messages over a shared channel. The fourth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with communication between multiple parties. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper discusses the transmission of messages over a shared channel.
